<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Line&nbsp;by&nbsp;line</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">.</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<blockquote>
<p>██/██/19██ a message</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This reads a little strange to me, I'd either add &quot;On&quot; to the beginning or make the date a heading somehow</p>
<blockquote>
<p>observatory by a radio telescope</p>
</blockquote>
<p>via a radio telescope?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>a space research station [REDACTED]</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Is this meant to be <em>the</em> space research station or just space research station, unless it's not the name of the space research station that's redacted</p>
<blockquote>
<p>██/██/19██ the following emails</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Same as before</p>
<blockquote>
<p>are similar to what we use to communicate with Foundation satellites and probes.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I'd personally change &quot;what we use&quot; to &quot;those we use&quot; or something similar.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>We were unable to pinpoint the location due to their proximity.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>its proximity?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>as there was no research conducted during that time</p>
</blockquote>
<p>being conducted?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Attached find the decrypted message.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This may be intentional for purposes of brevity but if not I'd write &quot;I have attached the decrypted message&quot; or at least &quot;find attached&quot;</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Log files were updated shortly</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This sentence doesn't make sense to me, updated immediately? Will be updated shortly?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>investigating into this incident</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I'd say the &quot;into&quot; is unnecessary here</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Although, if we did get lucky,</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Same here with the &quot;did&quot; - although I may be wrong</p>
<blockquote>
<p>They did not tell exactly what</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Say exactly what? Tell me exactly what?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>hug you through hundreds of millions of kilometers.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I don't know what to suggest for this but to me it reads strange</p>
<blockquote>
<p>take it in stride</p>
</blockquote>
<p>In my stride would be more traditional, even though in stride does work.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>you no longer are there.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Are no longer there might read a bit better</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>Some or even most of these may be intentional and my personal preference is getting in the way but I thought I'd be specific as possible.</p>

							</div>

								
