																		Supposedly
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/minjujube" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1677922); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1677922&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610163607" alt="Minjujube" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1677922)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/minjujube" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1677922); return false;" >Minjujube</a></span> <span class="odate time_1444383670 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">09 Oct 2015 09:41</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2388837">
									

<p>Supposedly is an adverb that is used to indicate that an event may or not have occurred with the common implication that the writer does not believe the event occurred at all. My suggestion to make it sound more clinical (and please feel free to disregard if the use of this word was deliberate):</p>
<p>Original: &quot;Supposedly, the signal originated from a space research station [REDACTED] &#8230;&quot;</p>
<p>Suggestion: &quot;The signal may have originated from the vicinity of the space research station&#8230;&quot;</p>
<p>Original: &quot;Supposedly, yours was the only telescope to detect this signal, although several facilities with low information availability remain to be checked.&quot;</p>
<p>Suggestion: &quot;Your telescope is the only one that has detected this signal so far; we, however, have yet to verify with some of the facilities that are not up to speed with rapid information parsing.&quot;</p>
<p>Note: Although I tried to keep with the original formatting, I definitely added my own interpretation of the spirit of the sentences. Again, feel free to use or not.</p>

							</div>

								
