			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2388859">
									

<p>OK, let me rephrase it.<br />
First original: &quot;The signal came from somewhere. It looks like it came from space station X, but we're not sure about it&quot;. Maybe I should have used &quot;presumably&quot; in this case.</p>
<p>Second original: &quot;We believe no other telescopes detected the signal at all, although we did not yet check all the facilities - some hard-to-reach ones are yet to be checked&quot;. Maybe these facilities are distant and/or do not have embedded Foundation agents.</p>

